<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-20T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-20T09:00:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1206: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-20T12:00:00-02:00">February 20,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 20—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. My telegram No. 27, February 18, 3 p.m. Major Sackville will leave by
                            Pan Air February 25th reaching Para 27th where Brazilian Government’s
                            facilities will begin. His cable address will be American Consul
                            Pará.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>